sonusSoftwareUpgradeServicesMIB.name: sonusSoftwareUpgradeServicesMIB
sonusSoftwareUpgradeServicesMIB.contactinfo: Customer Support Sonus Networks, Inc, 5 carlisle Road Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: 978-692-8999 Fax: 978-392-9118 E-mail: cs.snmp@sonusnet.com
sonusSoftwareUpgradeServicesMIB.description: The MIB Module for Software Upgrade Configuration.

SonusSoftwareUpgradeState.name: SonusSoftwareUpgradeState
SonusSoftwareUpgradeState.description: Represents the different states in LSWU FSM. (Internal use only)

sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnTable.name: sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnTable
sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnTable.description: This table specifies the software upgrade configuration.

sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnShelfIndex.name: sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnShelfIndex
sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnShelfIndex.description: The shelf index of this software upgrade entry.

sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnInit.name: sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnInit
sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnInit.description: Initialize the software upgrade, verify software image availability, check for unsupported features. The feature check can be disabled by setting sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnOverrideFeatureCheck in the same request. This MIB object can only be set through the CLI, and only by a user with admin privileges; it always reads as ready(1).

sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnUpgradeNow.name: sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnUpgradeNow
sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnUpgradeNow.description: Initiate the software upgrade of the specified shelf now. This MIB object can only be set through the CLI, and only by a user with admin privileges; it always reads as ready(1).

sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnHalt.name: sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnHalt
sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnHalt.description: Halt the software upgrade in progress. This MIB object can only be set through the CLI, and only by a user with admin privileges; it always reads as ready(1).

sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnCommitDirectory.name: sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnCommitDirectory
sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnCommitDirectory.description: Commit the new software distribution directory name into NVS. This MIB object can only be set by a user with admin privileges; it always reads as ready(1).

sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnDirectory.name: sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnDirectory
sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnDirectory.description: The new software distribution directory name. This MIB object can only be set by a user with admin privileges.

sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnOverrideFeatureCh.name: sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnOverrideFeatureCheck
sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnOverrideFeatureCh.description: Ignore the check for unsupported features (i.e. features that would prevent a software upgrade from occurring) during initialization. This MIB object must be set with sonusSwUpgradeShelfAdmnInit in the same request. This MIB object can only be set through the CLI, and only by a user with admin privileges; it always reads as ready(1).

sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatTable.name: sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatTable
sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatTable.description: This table contains status information about the software upgrade on a shelf.

sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatShelfIndex.name: sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatShelfIndex
sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatShelfIndex.description: Identifies the target shelf within the node.

sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatStatus.name: sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatStatus
sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatStatus.description: Indicates the software upgrade status of the shelf.

sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatCurSlot.name: sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatCurSlot
sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatCurSlot.description: Identifies the slot currently being upgraded with new software.

sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatSlotRemain.name: sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatSlotRemain
sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatSlotRemain.description: Identifies number of slots within the shelf remained to be upgraded.

sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatDuration.name: sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatDuration
sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatDuration.description: Indicates the duration of the software upgrade in seconds.

sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatStartTime.name: sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatStartTime
sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatStartTime.description: Indicates the start time of the software upgrade

sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatLastReason.name: sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatLastReason
sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatLastReason.description: Indicates the exit reason of the last live software upgrade.

sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatLastState.name: sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatLastState
sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatLastState.description: Indicates the last state of the LSWU FSM. (Internal use only)

sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatState.name: sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatState
sonusSwUpgradeShelfStatState.description: Indicates the current state of the LSWU FSM. (Internal use only)

sonusSwUpgradeSlotStatTable.name: sonusSwUpgradeSlotStatTable
sonusSwUpgradeSlotStatTable.description: This table contains status information about the software upgrade on a shelf.

sonusSwUpgradeSlotStatShelfIndex.name: sonusSwUpgradeSlotStatShelfIndex
sonusSwUpgradeSlotStatShelfIndex.description: Identifies the target shelf within the node.

sonusSwUpgradeSlotStatSlotIndex.name: sonusSwUpgradeSlotStatSlotIndex
sonusSwUpgradeSlotStatSlotIndex.description: Identifies the target slot within the shelf.

sonusSwUpgradeSlotStatStatus.name: sonusSwUpgradeSlotStatStatus
sonusSwUpgradeSlotStatStatus.description: Identifies the software upgrade status of a slot.

sonusSwUpgradeSlotStatVersion.name: sonusSwUpgradeSlotStatVersion
sonusSwUpgradeSlotStatVersion.description: The software version available for upgrade on the slot.

sonusSoftwareUpgradeInitiatedNotificatio.name: sonusSoftwareUpgradeInitiatedNotification
sonusSoftwareUpgradeInitiatedNotificatio.description: This trap indicates that a software upgrade to the specified Software Path directory has been initiated by the user for this shelf.

sonusSoftwareUpgradeTerminatedNotificati.name: sonusSoftwareUpgradeTerminatedNotification
sonusSoftwareUpgradeTerminatedNotificati.description: This trap indicates that a software upgrade to the specified Software Path directory has terminated in this shelf for the specified reason.

sonusSoftwareUpgradeSucceededNotificatio.name: sonusSoftwareUpgradeSucceededNotification
sonusSoftwareUpgradeSucceededNotificatio.description: This trap indicates that a software upgrade to the specified Software Path directory has succeeded in this shelf for the specified reason.
